===Noun===
'''[[grammar]] [[school]]'''
#(''mostly British'') a [[secondary]] school that stresses [[academic]] over [[practical]] or [[vocational]] [[education]]; until recent times was open to those [[pupil]]s who had passed the [[11-plus examination]]
#(''archaic'') a school which teaches its pupils the grammar-system of a European language, especially [[Latin]] and [[Greek]]

